This paper discusses a data ingestion framework for enriching big data with complex operations and adapting to changes in reference data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses on data management and performance evaluation, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IR and cs.DS.
